This paper deals with the logical consistency of robotic agents, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics (RO). The paper also discusses the use of model checking, which is a technique commonly used in formal methods (LO) for verifying the correctness of software and hardware systems. Additionally, the paper presents algorithms for performing consistency checks, which falls under software engineering (SE) and programming languages (PL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LO, cs.SE, and cs.PL, in that order.
